{# Single humanized chip — shared by the Today and Review Queue cards.

   Renders one ``HumanFlag`` as a chip carrying:
     * the human title + brief detail as visible text,
     * the raw flag code in ``data-flag-code`` so workers can grep
       devtools when something looks wrong,
     * the raw code repeated in ``title`` so hovering surfaces the
       machine identifier.

   Severity band drives the chip color via ``hf.chip_class`` (set by
   ``aegis.web._flag_labels``): decline -> ``bad``, material -> ``warn``,
   look_closer -> ``info``, context -> bare ``chip``.

   When ``hf.cluster_signals`` is populated (only for
   ``fraud_cluster_triangulated``), the chip is wrapped in a ``<details>``
   so clicking it expands an inline list of the humanized constituent
   signals. CSS gives the wrapper ``display: contents`` so the chip stays
   inline in the surrounding flag-list flexbox until the worker opens it.

   Inputs:
     - hf: HumanFlag (in scope from the calling for-loop)
#}
{% if hf.cluster_signals %}
<details class="chip-cluster">
  <summary><span class="chip {{ hf.chip_class }}" data-flag-code="{{ hf.code }}" title="{{ hf.code }}">{{ hf.title }}{% if hf.detail %} <span class="chip-detail">· {{ hf.detail }}</span>{% endif %}</span></summary>
  <ul class="chip-cluster-signals">
    {% for sig in hf.cluster_signals %}
      <li><span class="chip {{ sig.chip_class }}" data-flag-code="{{ sig.code }}" title="{{ sig.code }}">{{ sig.title }}{% if sig.detail %} <span class="chip-detail">· {{ sig.detail }}</span>{% endif %}</span></li>
    {% endfor %}
  </ul>
</details>
{% else %}
<span class="chip {{ hf.chip_class }}" data-flag-code="{{ hf.code }}" title="{{ hf.code }}">{{ hf.title }}{% if hf.detail %} <span class="chip-detail">· {{ hf.detail }}</span>{% endif %}</span>
{% endif %}
